"Bcc," on the other hand, stands for "blind carbon copy." It is used when you want to send a copy of the email to one or more additional recipients without revealing the email addresses of the other recipients. This is useful when you want to send an email to a large group of people and you don't want to clutter up their inboxes with a list of email addresses.

In both cases, the recipients that you are sending "cc" or "bcc" to will not be able to see the email addresses of the other recipients. However, in early 1917, Germany announced its policy of unrestricted submarine warfare, which posed a direct threat to American merchant ships and citizens. This, combined with a series of other events and diplomatic incidents, eventually led the U.S. to declare war on Germany.

In the United Kingdom, when a public holiday falls on a weekend (i.e., on a Saturday or a Sunday), the public holiday is usually observed on the following Monday (unless the Monday is also a bank holiday, in which case it is observed on the Tuesday). If the public holiday falls on a weekday, then it is typically observed on the day itself.

In general, if a public holiday falls on a day that you would normally work, you may be entitled to a day off in lieu (also known as a "floaters' holiday" or "substitute holiday"). This means that you would receive an extra day's leave (paid or unpaid, depending on your employment contract) to be taken at a later date.

However, whether or not you are entitled to a day off in lieu of a public holiday depends on your specific employment circumstances and the terms of your contract. Some employers may choose to give their employees a day off in lieu of a public holiday, even if they are not legally required to do so, as a benefit or gesture of goodwill. It is important to check your employment contract or speak to your employer to determine your specific entitlements.

The Salvation Army arrived in Australia in 1880, when its founder, William Booth, sent a team of officers to Melbourne to begin its work amongst the poor and disenfranchised. The organization quickly gained popularity and expanded its operations across the country, establishing a network of centers that provided a range of social services, including education, health care, and support for people struggling with addiction and homelessness. Today, the Salvation Army is a major provider of social welfare services in Australia, with a presence in every state and territory.
